    <item>
      <title>Enable gx in NvChad</title>
      
      
      
      
        
      <category>Neovim</category>
        
      
      <description>&lt;h1&gt;Enable &lt;code&gt;gx&lt;/code&gt; in NvChad&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The command &lt;code&gt;gx&lt;/code&gt; opens the filename under the the cursor with &lt;code&gt;vim.ui.open()&lt;/code&gt;
(see &lt;a href=&#34;https://neovim.io/doc/user/pi_netrw.html#netrw-gx&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;:help netrw-gx&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;{target=&#34;_blank&#34;}).
Then handling is provided by the internal &lt;code&gt;netrw&lt;/code&gt; plugin. This plugin is
disabled when using &lt;a href=&#34;../../tools/vi/neovim/index.md&#34;&gt;NvChad&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <link>https://dreknix.github.io/wiki/blog/2023/11/21/enable-gx-in-nvchad.html</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 21 Nov 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <source url="https://dreknix.github.io/wiki/feed_rss_created.xml">dreknix - Documentation</source>
      
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://dreknix.github.io/wiki/blog/2023/11/21/enable-gx-in-nvchad.html</guid>
      
    </item>
    
